      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Letting go means not relying on others to carry the weight, not trying to become your kids' personal caregivers. It means setting healthy boundaries, like not rescheduling appointments at the last minute or not expecting them to handle your overflow anxiety. By taking responsibility for your own healing, you'll be able to adapt and grow, becoming less of a burden and more of a blessing to them. This way, you'll be able to coexist without being a constant source of stress.",
      "source": "target",
